WEBVTT

00:09.593 --> 00:12.388
Hello.

00:12.596 --> 00:14.098
Yeah.

00:14.306 --> 00:17.351
Uh, we're going to go
on a mission right now.

00:17.560 --> 00:19.812
Uh, so will you come with me?

00:22.648 --> 00:23.691
Oh.

00:23.899 --> 00:25.026
You will.

00:32.575 --> 00:33.993
So I'm going down
the street, and I get a hit.

00:35.453 --> 00:36.620
Heath, Heath, Heath...

00:36.829 --> 00:38.914
and, sure enough,
the next day, I said,

00:39.123 --> 00:40.249
"I'm going to hear about
something...Heath.

00:40.458 --> 00:41.208
There's something going on."

00:41.417 --> 00:42.543
The next day, I got your email.

00:45.546 --> 00:50.718
I honestly think
that the earth is off axis.

00:50.926 --> 00:51.886
I think there's something

00:52.094 --> 00:57.433
that is universally
out of alignment...

00:57.641 --> 00:58.809
with what happened.

00:59.018 --> 01:02.730
I'm not supposed to be
talking about this with you.

01:02.938 --> 01:03.814
This is...

01:04.022 --> 01:05.691
This isn't supposed
to be being made.

01:05.900 --> 01:07.443
This is fucked up.

01:07.651 --> 01:08.944
Like, this is not something

01:09.153 --> 01:10.946
that is supposed
to be happening right now.

01:12.740 --> 01:14.742
♪ I'm tearing up ♪

01:14.950 --> 01:18.162
Heath was
the most alive human...

01:18.370 --> 01:21.248
and if it wasn't on the edge,
it didn't interest him.

01:21.457 --> 01:25.836
If there wasn't a risk,
some type of risk involved,

01:26.045 --> 01:28.130
he had no time for it.

01:29.673 --> 01:32.009
He went all the way out
in the time that he had.

01:32.218 --> 01:33.928
He went all the way to the edge.

01:36.055 --> 01:39.183
Some people
are just bigger than...

01:42.103 --> 01:43.062
the world has room for.

01:44.647 --> 01:46.774
♪ Still alive who you love ♪

01:52.822 --> 01:54.865
♪ Still alive who you love ♪

02:00.704 --> 02:02.414
He already
had this vision

02:02.623 --> 02:03.999
as to where he was going to be.

02:04.208 --> 02:06.877
He had these little shiny stars
on the ceiling

02:07.086 --> 02:08.336
that he put up
in this old house.

02:08.545 --> 02:10.923
He said, you know,
"That's where I'm going to be."

02:11.132 --> 02:13.843
He said, "I'm going
to be in the film industry,"

02:14.051 --> 02:15.553
and he said, "I'm going
to be a film actor."

02:17.555 --> 02:18.347
Heath used to follow

02:18.556 --> 02:19.682
his sister Kate, you know,

02:19.890 --> 02:22.226
all her productions
that she was at at school.

02:22.434 --> 02:26.897
Heath being in the front row
like this, for every single one.

02:27.106 --> 02:28.190
"That's what I want to do.

02:28.399 --> 02:29.400
I can't wait
'til I can do that."

02:32.570 --> 02:34.029
He excelled
in everything he did.

02:34.238 --> 02:36.448
Chess was his biggest passion.

02:37.741 --> 02:39.702
"Please,
just let me win one game.

02:39.910 --> 02:42.997
Why are you just, like,
thinking of it at this level?"

02:43.205 --> 02:44.832
Great at art,

02:45.040 --> 02:46.375
amazing athlete...

02:46.584 --> 02:47.918
Heath used to get into scraps.

02:48.127 --> 02:48.794
He was a good fighter.

02:51.714 --> 02:53.132
I remember the conversations

02:53.340 --> 02:54.842
about Heath wanting
to leave school

02:55.050 --> 02:56.760
and travel across Australia.

02:56.969 --> 02:58.846
I was quite shocked
at the time because he was 17.

02:59.054 --> 03:01.348
It was like trying
to settle a wild stallion

03:01.557 --> 03:02.474
at the time.

03:02.683 --> 03:04.476
You may as well
make a friend of them

03:04.685 --> 03:07.021
and support them
as best you can and love them,

03:07.229 --> 03:09.148
and let's hope
that everything turns out.

03:09.356 --> 03:12.193
I've got nothing
to run away from in Perth.

03:12.401 --> 03:13.277
I love my family.

03:13.485 --> 03:15.196
I love my friends.
I love the city.

03:15.404 --> 03:18.073
It's just there was all this
going on outside of that,

03:18.282 --> 03:19.658
and I just had to be part of it.

03:19.867 --> 03:21.660
Heath and Trevor,

03:21.869 --> 03:23.037
they were out
to conquer the world,

03:23.245 --> 03:24.622
the two of them.

03:24.830 --> 03:27.499
Pretty much waited for the day
for me to finish school,

03:27.708 --> 03:29.126
and he was like,
"Let's go to Sydney."

03:31.045 --> 03:32.630
It was literally
jumping in our car

03:32.838 --> 03:35.341
and planting the foot down
and just bolting out.

03:35.549 --> 03:37.927
I wanted to just get out there
and do it.

03:39.470 --> 03:40.137
♪ March, march ♪

03:41.305 --> 03:42.514
♪ Said march, march ♪

03:42.723 --> 03:44.516
From there,
things moved on pretty quick.

03:44.725 --> 03:47.186
♪ Fists in the air
as we march on ♪

03:47.394 --> 03:48.312
We're going to Bondi.

03:48.520 --> 03:49.230
We're just starting there.

03:49.438 --> 03:50.356
Roll together.

03:50.564 --> 03:51.690
Come on in, boys and girls.

03:51.899 --> 03:52.983
You get what you want.

03:53.192 --> 03:54.026
He took me
to all these auditions,

03:54.235 --> 03:55.319
all these interviews...

03:55.527 --> 03:56.987
Never asked.
He just did it.

03:57.196 --> 04:00.241
He got a role
in an American TV series, Roar.

04:00.449 --> 04:02.034
He had the lead role.

04:02.243 --> 04:03.244
Action!

04:03.452 --> 04:04.620
You'll be lucky
if you live that long.

04:04.828 --> 04:05.871
Great. Cut!

04:06.080 --> 04:07.539
Now he's an actor.
It was serious.

04:07.748 --> 04:08.916
We went to the Gold Coast.

04:09.124 --> 04:11.252
We were put up in a two-
bedroom high-rise apartment

04:11.460 --> 04:12.628
overlooking the ocean.

04:12.836 --> 04:15.089
Money, as a 17-year-old,
was impressive.

04:15.297 --> 04:16.339
"Wow, here we are."

04:18.926 --> 04:19.718
Everything
kept moving forward.

04:19.927 --> 04:20.803
Hello.

04:21.011 --> 04:21.720
Lisa was a real woman,

04:21.928 --> 04:23.889
very classy.

04:24.098 --> 04:25.557
He looked up to her.

04:25.766 --> 04:26.475
They fell in love
really quickly.

04:26.684 --> 04:27.601
She guided him.

04:27.810 --> 04:29.061
She could see
the potential in him.

04:29.270 --> 04:30.521
Lisa, where are we going?

04:30.729 --> 04:33.607
She took his hand
and opened a lot of doors.

04:33.816 --> 04:34.733
He followed her from Australia.

04:34.942 --> 04:36.443
She was, like, "Come to L.A."

04:36.652 --> 04:38.028
Dumb-looking photo.

04:38.237 --> 04:39.154
♪ We march on ♪

